### Form Handling

-   Use shadcn/ui Form components for all forms
-   Implement Zod schemas for form validation
-   Use FormField pattern for form inputs
-   Structure forms with proper FormControl components
-   Follow consistent form layout patterns

Example form structure:

```typescript
<Form {...form}>
    <form onSubmit={(e) => void form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)(e)}>
        <FormField
            control={form.control}
            name="fieldName"
            render={({ field }) => (
                <FormItem>
                    <FormLabel>Field Label</FormLabel>
                    <FormControl>
                        <Input {...field} />
                    </FormControl>
                    <FormMessage />
                </FormItem>
            )}
        />
    </form>
</Form>
```

Key components to use:

-   Form - Wrapper for the form context
-   FormField - Field-level validation and state
-   FormItem - Container for form elements
-   FormLabel - Accessible label
-   FormControl - Input wrapper
-   FormMessage - Error message display
-   FormDescription - Optional field description

